# License policy — read before porting any code

This library is **MIT**. Every line you write or translate must be compatible.
When in doubt, do not copy — reimplement from public documentation.

## Source licenses: what you may do

- **Port / translate freely:** ISC or MIT/Expat only.
  - `ares` (ISC), `SameBoy` (MIT/Expat).
- **Reference only — read to understand, NEVER translate or copy structure:**
  GPL / MPL / LGPL sources. `Mesen 2`, `mGBA`, `Stella`, `blastem`, `tamalib`,
  `NanoBoyAdvance`, `Nuked-OPL3`.
- **Do not open at all:** non-commercial licenses. `snes9x`, `Genesis Plus GX`.

## Clean-room discipline

- Prefer hardware manuals and dev wikis (Pandocs, NESdev, GBATEK, fullsnes,
  Epson manual) over any emulator source.
- For a "reference only" source: describe behavior in your own words from docs,
  then implement. Do not transcribe its code, variable names, or table layouts.
- `consoles.csv` records the sanctioned reference + license per system. Trust it.

## ROMs & BIOS

- This repo **never** contains or distributes commercial ROMs or BIOS files.
- Test inputs come via git submodules under `tests/roms/` (permissive only).
- Golden images under `tests/golden/` are our own rendered output — fine to commit.
- Never implement or assist copy-protection circumvention.
